The Catholic lay faithful in Nigeria, under the aegis of the Catholic Laity Council of Nigeria (CLCN) has called for action over the murder of two priests, Rev. Fr. Joseph Gor and Rev. Fr. Felix Tyolaha in Benue State. The priests together with a catechist and several other parishioners were killed by gunmen at the St. Ignatius Catholic Church, Ukpor-Mbalom in Gwer Local Government Area of the state. The National President, Sir Thomas Folu Adekoya and National Secretary-General, Sir Henry H. Yunkwap in a statement yesterday demanded that the killers of the two clerics and the other worshipers be immediately fished out and made to pay for their crime.